00:00:03.890 --> 00:00:06.405
Here I have a card,

00:00:06.405 --> 00:00:07.770
but it doesn't look good.

00:00:07.770 --> 00:00:10.620
Why? Because of
the spacing here,

00:00:10.620 --> 00:00:12.270
the content cannot breathe.

00:00:12.270 --> 00:00:13.740
Therefore, I need to modify

00:00:13.740 --> 00:00:15.660
the spacing between
these elements,

00:00:15.660 --> 00:00:16.800
as I mentioned before,

00:00:16.800 --> 00:00:18.165
when it comes to spacing,

00:00:18.165 --> 00:00:20.025
we have two main components.

00:00:20.025 --> 00:00:22.215
We have the margin
and the padding.

00:00:22.215 --> 00:00:25.230
The margin is the space
outside the element,

00:00:25.230 --> 00:00:28.375
and the padding is the
space inside an element.

00:00:28.375 --> 00:00:30.605
So let's take a look here.

00:00:30.605 --> 00:00:32.155
I'm going to select my card.

00:00:32.155 --> 00:00:33.260
If I want to add

00:00:33.260 --> 00:00:35.930
some breathing room for
these texts block here,

00:00:35.930 --> 00:00:38.195
I'm going to select
that and I can add

00:00:38.195 --> 00:00:41.705
left padding and right
padding just like that.

00:00:41.705 --> 00:00:43.850
Alternatively, what I can do is

00:00:43.850 --> 00:00:46.745
select the card and
add the padding.

00:00:46.745 --> 00:00:49.130
However, this padding applies to

00:00:49.130 --> 00:00:52.115
all the elements
inside this card,

00:00:52.115 --> 00:00:56.255
to all the children of
these card diblock.

00:00:56.255 --> 00:00:57.590
Let's give it a try.

00:00:57.590 --> 00:00:58.940
Just like that.

00:00:58.940 --> 00:01:00.455
And there we go.

00:01:00.455 --> 00:01:01.850
But this is not what I want.

00:01:01.850 --> 00:01:03.515
I'm going to undo the process

00:01:03.515 --> 00:01:05.345
and I'm going to
select the textblock,

00:01:05.345 --> 00:01:06.980
and I'm going to add 20 pixels

00:01:06.980 --> 00:01:08.465
and left and right padding.

00:01:08.465 --> 00:01:11.510
However, it's very tedious
and time-consuming

00:01:11.510 --> 00:01:14.885
to add the padding for
each side one by one.

00:01:14.885 --> 00:01:17.300
Therefore, I can hold
down the Option key on

00:01:17.300 --> 00:01:19.894
Mac and Alt key on Windows,

00:01:19.894 --> 00:01:21.590
and then click and drag to

00:01:21.590 --> 00:01:23.990
adjust the padding
for opposing sides.

00:01:23.990 --> 00:01:25.190
Just like that.

00:01:25.190 --> 00:01:29.315
If I want to change the padding
for all sides like top,

00:01:29.315 --> 00:01:30.965
bottom, left, and right.

00:01:30.965 --> 00:01:33.125
Instead of Option or Alt key,

00:01:33.125 --> 00:01:35.000
I need to hold down
the Shift key on

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:38.465
my keyboard and then click
and drag, check it out.

00:01:38.465 --> 00:01:40.340
That saves a lot of time.

00:01:40.340 --> 00:01:41.840
But what about the margin?

00:01:41.840 --> 00:01:45.050
Let me set the top
padding here to zero.

00:01:45.050 --> 00:01:48.170
And I'm going to select
this heading this time.

00:01:48.170 --> 00:01:51.455
Instead of padding, I'm
going to change the margin,

00:01:51.455 --> 00:01:53.840
the bottom margin, as
I mentioned before,

00:01:53.840 --> 00:01:57.125
the margin is the space
outside of an element.

00:01:57.125 --> 00:01:59.960
Therefore, I'm going
to increase that by

00:01:59.960 --> 00:02:04.310
ten pixels and the top margin
by ten pixels as well.

00:02:04.310 --> 00:02:06.905
Alright, it looks
much better now.

00:02:06.905 --> 00:02:10.400
Alright, now this card
is inside a container.

00:02:10.400 --> 00:02:13.445
If I take it outside this
container for a second,

00:02:13.445 --> 00:02:15.995
you can see that it
touches the edges.

00:02:15.995 --> 00:02:20.060
If I want to align it to
the center of my section,

00:02:20.060 --> 00:02:22.655
let me remove this
container for a second.

00:02:22.655 --> 00:02:26.225
If I want to center it both
horizontally and vertically,

00:02:26.225 --> 00:02:27.860
I have some options.

00:02:27.860 --> 00:02:29.960
The first option
is that I can go

00:02:29.960 --> 00:02:32.600
ahead and set the
margin manually,

00:02:32.600 --> 00:02:34.775
just like this, which is nuts,

00:02:34.775 --> 00:02:37.730
a good option and you
shouldn't try that ever.

00:02:37.730 --> 00:02:40.865
The reason is when you
set the margin manually,

00:02:40.865 --> 00:02:43.595
it may look good on one device.

00:02:43.595 --> 00:02:46.595
However, if you go to
the iPad breakpoint,

00:02:46.595 --> 00:02:49.505
you can see that it's not
centered because it still

00:02:49.505 --> 00:02:52.580
has a 435 pixel margin.

00:02:52.580 --> 00:02:55.250
So you should never
do that, are right.

